'''Lododo''' alo '''Lododowo''' (Eŋlisigbeme [[:en:Proverb|Proverbs]] ) nye nya siwo miegblɔna kuɖe agbe aɖe si ame ɖe nɔ la ŋu. Enu enu la, nya siawo nyea nuxɔxlɔ̃ na amewo eye wodea sesẽ lãme na nunyuiwɔlawo.

==Lododo ƒe kpɔɖeŋu aɖewo==

Lododo ƒe kpɔɖeŋu aɖewoe nye:
*Abɔ mekpe na wu ata o.<ref name="agbemenu">{{cite web|url=http://afriprov.org/images/afriprov/books/ewe100proverbs.pdf |title=A Collection of Ewe Proverbs |author=Cephas Yao Agbemenu |date=1 November 2010 |access-date=7 July 2021 }}</ref>
*Ada ata so ha, mɔ le eme.<ref name="agbemenu"/>
*Adeɖitsa kple lãɖitsa ye do na go.<ref name="sepatm">{{cite web|url=https://enam98.wordpress.com/2016/12/18/some-ewe-proverbs-and-their-meanings/ |title=Some Ewe proverbs and their meanings |access-date=7 July 2021}}</ref><ref name="agra"/>
*Adzofu di aha ʋuu, amatsi woku ne.<ref name="agbemenu"/>
*Afi ɖu ke, ke mevɔna le efe ŋkume o.<ref name="agbemenu"/>
*Afia ɖe kpɔkpɔ nyo wu ya me kpɔkpɔ.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Afɔ me yi na nugbe eye atagba tsi na aƒe o.<ref name="sepatm"/><ref name="agra"/>
*Afɔ tu de, memuna de o.<ref name="agbemenu"/>
*Aƒevemegbɔ, gbɔdome wòtsina.<ref name="agbemenu"/>
*Agaga lolo me ƒle na agaga eve ƒe nu o.<ref name="sepatm"/><ref name="agra"/>
*Agalã be ne yele axa dzi zɔm hã menye mɔ yebu o.<ref name="africanmanners"/>
*Agbavi tɔ meɖuna anyanya o.<ref name="agbemenu"/>
*Agbebaɖaa metia agbetɔ o.<ref name="agbemenu"/>
*Agbenɔxevi megbea fu megbea fuma to o.
*Agɔ biã, de biã, gake agɔ me daa ami o.<ref name="agbemenu"/>
*Agɔbaya meƒoanu dzro o. Yae ɖo agɔme.<ref name="agbemenu"/>
*Ahlɔ̃e medoa nyi fɔkpa o.
*Ako be ne meɖi ʋu o hã, kpɔ ye ƒe ble me ɖa.<ref name="agbemenu"/>
*Akɔta gbadzaa melɔ̃ na halã o.<ref name="agbemenu"/>
*Alegeli be ekpo ɖe megbetɔwo dzi.
*Ame aɖe me de na deku eve alɔme eye lɔ na kui o.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Ame eve metsia bome o.
*Ame ŋutɔ ƒe aba vuvu me di na nya na ame o.<ref name="sepatm"/><ref name="agra"/>
*Ame ŋutɔ ƒe golomehɛ ye si na ame.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Ame ye nɔ na ame ŋuti hafi wo nye na zami.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Anyigba sese gake agama ɖo na afɔ anyi blewuu.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Ati ɖeka me wɔna ave o.<ref name="sepatm"/><ref name="agra">{{cite web |url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/313063218_Ewe_Proverbs_-_A_Source_of_Imagery_for_Textile_Designs |title=Ewe Proverbs - A Source of Imagery for Textile Designs |author=Florence Emefa Agra |date=March 2016 |access-date=7 July 2021}}</ref>
*Ati gɔglɔ dzi wonɔ na hafi tso dzɔdzɔ ɛtɔ.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Avu ɖu ƒu me dua ga o.
*Avu ɖuna avutɔ.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Avulélae xɔa kɔ.
*Bafa medoa kalẽ ha ɖa o.<ref name="africanmanners">{{cite web|url=https://africanmanners.wordpress.com/2012/07/07/ewe-proverbs-ghana-and-togo-41-in-total/ |title=Ewe Proverbs 
 July (Ghana and Togo): 41 in Total |publisher=African Matters |date=7 July 2012 |access-date=7 July 2021}}</ref>
*Dadi be nusi avu kpɔ hafi do ɣli, ye yekpɔna mia ŋku ɖedzi.
*Detsi vivi ye hea zikpui.<ref name="africanmanners"/>
*Dɔbu me ɖu na nu eye dɔbu de na asi o.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Du aɖe me gbede ʋuyɔvi wòzuna le du bubu me.<ref name="africanmanners"/>
*Du aɖewo ƒe gbagba ye nye du aɖewo ƒe tutu.<ref name="sepatm"/><ref name="agra"/>
*Du sia du kple eƒe koklokoko.<ref name="africanmanners"/><ref name="agra"/>
*Dumenyo mesɔa aƒe o.
*Dzea ʋa ɖia, aʋa mesi nɛ o.
*Dzigbɔdi wo tsɔ xɔa nu le fia si.
*Ɖe wo ta na hafi zɔ na.
*Ɖevi gba abɔbɔgo megba na klogo o.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Ɖevi ka aple gã mekaa nya gã o.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Fu kple dzidzɔ la nɔviwo wonye.<ref name="africanmanners"/><ref name="agra"/>
*Gbɔ̃ tokpo ye xlɔŋu via.
*Gbɔ̃sikɛ menɔa gbɔ̃ ŋgɔ o.
*Ge me tu na xɔ na aɖaba o.<ref name="sepatm"/><ref name="agra"/>
*Gli matsɔ amegbɔ wome dea mee o.
*Ha be mele lolo me o, tsivivi mee wole.
*Ha be ŋdi tsie nye nyia.
*Hadzimatso la, akaye wo gba na.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Haho metsɔa tɔ o.
*Klo be wó be ye neva kpɔ yegbe, ye na be ye ƒe ta tsi gome.
*Klugã me nye vigã o.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Koklo be kɔ gbɔe agbe le.
*Koklo be ɣlidola wo xɔna na.
*Koklo metsɔa ƒu dome vea avu o.
*Kokloxɔ vuvu mekpe na ŋu na koklo o.
*Koklotsu eve wo le adzre wɔm, gake wo le wo nɔɛwoƒe ŋkukpɔm.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Kɔdzo Dei be yele Blu fiam gake yeƒe ŋku le Eʋegbe ŋu.<ref name="africanmanners"/>
*Lagla xoxo me ƒo na detsi o.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Makpɔƒle metsia asime o.
*Melege melegea ɖewo tsia ɖi ame.
*Mɔdidi megbea du nu yi na o.
*Mɔse ƒe ye nye xɔme.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Ne abɔbɔ yi nu gbe la, klo gbɔ wo dze na.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Ne ame aɖe le ʋu tome ƒom la, egbɔ na ʋu la ŋutɔ ƒoge.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Ne ati aɖe le nya dim ɣesiaɣi le fíáwo ŋuti la, mumu ye le dzrom.<ref name="sepatm"/><ref name="agra"/>
*Ne edidi ʋu hã etsɔ ko woyɔne.
*Ne lo lolo ʋuu hã la, azimevi ko wonye.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Ne lɔ̃lɔ sakɔ la menya tuna o.<ref name="agra"/>
*Ne ŋkugbagbatɔ aɖe be ye le ekpe da ge la, eƒe afɔ le ekpe la dzi xoxo.<ref name="sepatm"/><ref name="agra"/>
*Nuɣeɖutɔ me nyana be dɔto o.<ref name="sepatm"/><ref name="agra"/>
*Nunya adidoe asi me tu ne o.
*Nunyui wɔla ƒe ta me tsia bame o.
*Sabala le nogo gake mɔ le eme.
*Safui sese ye ʋu na gaʋɔ.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Ta ɖeka meɖea aɖaŋu o.
*Ta menɔanyi klo dɔa kuku o. 
*Tɔmedela ye gba na ze.<ref name="sepatm"/><ref name="agra"/>
*Tre eve nɔ tɔŋgɔ me gbe na gododo o.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Vi gbã abɔbɔgo me gbã klo go o.
*Vivi mevɔ na le agɔ kuŋu hafi wotsɔne ƒua gbe o.
*Vivɔɛ me nye na mi le ata dzi eye wo tsɔ na hɛ kpanaɛ o.<ref name="sepatm"/>
*Ʋutɔtrɔ ŋue wotrɔa ɣeɖuɖu ɖo.<ref name="africanmanners"/>
*Wome da kalami ɖe dadi gbɔ o.
*Zego yibɔ me ye akatsa ɣi la do go tso.<ref name="sepatm"/><ref name="agra"/>
*Zigã me nye fia o.<ref name="sepatm"/>

